          </list-item>
          <list-item id="o0525">
            <label>17.</label>
            <p id="p1290">The reason we created two columns for the header (e.g., NoBadName_Hit_Des or HitDescription) is to reduce ambiguity. A uniform header is needed when merging different databases. We also included the percentage identity and E-value for each type of BLAST search result, which can be easily compared. If two BLAST database hit descriptions are both without ‘bad words’, the one with lower E-value will be chosen.</p>
          </list-item>
        </list>
      </p>
